    "body": "In the end, the **observer** is the same as what we consider a normal node on the Ethereum network. \r\n\r\n- Connect to the sharded universe\r\n- Sync chains\r\n- Provide interface for users to interact with Ethereum. This could be via console or exposing RPC endpoints. \r\n\r\nEssentially, it has the same capabilities as a proposer or notary, but has no role. \r\nThis is the default state and there really is not much to design or define, in my opinion. ",
